In an earlier chapter, we have shown that an interesting subset of the Modular
 Group acts as a map of intervals to intervals, and can be enumerated as
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{Q\times\mathbb{N}}$
\end_inset 

 (that is, a subset of the Modular Group has a set-theoretic representation).
 In this chapter, we apply these ideas to a fractal curve studied by Weierstrass
