3-period Mode Locking
\layout Standard

Note that some chaotic maps are seen to have period-doubling paths to chaos
 that include a factor of three: viz.
 3,6,12,24,...
 I believe that this should be considered a manifestation of the fact that
 the modular group can be written as the free product of the two and three
 cycles 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{Z}_{2}$
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{Z}_{3}$
\end_inset 

.
